WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.475
This transactional route is a competitive weapon. It empowers you

00:00:04.475 --> 00:00:08.950
to retain customers struggling with limited departmental budgets by tapping

00:00:08.950 --> 00:00:13.425
into broader corporate funds. This reduction in buyer cost-sensitivity establishes

00:00:13.425 --> 00:00:17.900
a massive competitive advantage. Consider this scenario. A customer has

00:00:17.900 --> 00:00:22.375
no marketing budget but a massive AWS commit. Do you:

00:00:22.375 --> 00:00:26.850
A, discount heavily, or B, route through the Marketplace? The

00:00:26.850 --> 00:00:31.325
right move is B. Routing through the Marketplace taps into

00:00:31.325 --> 00:00:35.800
their existing cloud budget.
